ater","1 cucumber, peeled into ribbons (optional)","20 g alfalfa sprouts              (optional)","1 tsp black sesame seeds              (optional)"]}],"id":"r105368","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-EmSedUFrSEo\/XZafEUDIZZI\/AAAAAAAAgq4\/e6gLnXLejB04yfDWOIQQc8wW_oBYjj0cgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_h9UQ6nuakSrx6wrn.png","title":"Thai chicken balls with sweet chilli dipping sauce","publishedAt":"2016-07-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.5 g","fat":"10.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"14.1 g","calories":"939 kJ \/ 223 kcal"},"usefulItems":"serving bowl, bowl, baking paper","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own red curry paste, please refer to the recipe in <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em>."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","6 portions"]}